<div id="review_12570757" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/12570757" />
    <a title="Ritch" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/752707-ritch"><img alt="Ritch" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1199727132p2/752707.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/12570757?book_show_action=true">Jan 15, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ritch" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ritch" href="/user/show/752707-ritch">Ritch</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">People who start werewolf blogs, fans of high camp, perverts.</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer12570757" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3646495010152295704">The fact that this book even exists is so great, I can barely even contain myself. My friend M. Sweeney Lawless passed it on to me when I was working on a screenplay based on <a href='http://whatishappeningtome.blogspot.com/2004_10_01_archive.html' rel='nofollow noopener'>my werewolf blog</a>, and I fell in love, mainly with the huge balls it took the author to write this book. <br/><br/>From the Back Jacket: &quot;He is Michael Gallatin, master spy, lover-and werewolf. Able to change shape with the lightning speed, to kill silently with savage, snarling fury, he proved his talents against Rommel in Africa. An</span>
  <span id="freeText3646495010152295704" style="display:none">The fact that this book even exists is so great, I can barely even contain myself. My friend M. Sweeney Lawless passed it on to me when I was working on a screenplay based on <a href="http://whatishappeningtome.blogspot.com/2004_10_01_archive.html" rel="nofollow noopener">my werewolf blog</a>, and I fell in love, mainly with the huge balls it took the author to write this book. <br /><br />From the Back Jacket: "He is Michael Gallatin, master spy, lover-and werewolf. Able to change shape with the lightning speed, to kill silently with savage, snarling fury, he proved his talents against Rommel in Africa. And now he faces his most delicate, dangerous mission: to unravel the secret Nazi plan known as Iron Fist." <br /><br />This book is packed with werewolf vs nazi action, flashbacks to the Russian Revolution and a rather alarming number of graphic sex scenes. Oh, and it's 600 pages long. <br /><br />You heard me. <br /><br />A good 70 pages longer than 'Crime and Punishment.'<br /><br />In it's defense, there are considerably more murders in The Wolf's Hour, which eats up the page count. <br /><br />I've only read about 242 of them, and mostly stopped because my future wife begged me too, as I had a compulsive habit of reading the book in bed, giggling like an idiot, and then reading long passages aloud to her, usually about werewolves peeing on each other. <br /><br />Update: After writing this, I threw the book in my bag for my honeymoon, and I have about 100 pages left in it. The scene in which two werewolves have sex in both human and wolf form is particularly repellant. Right now, the werewolf is behind enemy lines in Norway, looking into an illegal SS chemical agent that they have been testing on humans. There is a hot blonde actress with him who suspects he is a werewolf. It's stupider than hell. <br /><br />Second Update: <br /><br />I finished this book, and Jesus, does the ending suck. Winston Churchill shows up, for Christ's sake. I knew that the ending was going to suck with about 60 pages left, but what- do you only read the first 540 pages of the werewolf spy novel and then put it down, saying, yeah- it's not that good? <br /><br />C'mon, man. <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3646495010152295704" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


